8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Smartsheet and Wrike AI share a solid foundation of core features including Task Management, Ai Assistant, Calendar, Collaboration. Interestingly, both platforms offer nearly identical feature sets. The difference lies more in the implementation quality and depth of each feature rather than feature availability itself. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Smartsheet holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Wrike AI scores 7/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Wrike AI comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Smartsheet begins at $9/mo. Wrike AI stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Smartsheet requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
