c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Smartsheet is best suited for PMOs, construction, enterprise operations, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Wrike AI, meanwhile, shines for enterprise teams, professional services, marketing ops, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2005, Smartsheet describes itself as \"Spreadsheet-based work management platform with AI automation for enterprises.\" Wrike AI, established in 2006, positions itself as \"Enterprise work management platform with AI-powered project intelligence.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Smartsheet** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to overall value and user satisfaction. However, this does not mean Wrike AI is a poor choice — far from it. Wrike AI excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise teams and professional services.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value familiar spreadsheet interface, go with Smartsheet. If strong enterprise features and security matters more to you, Wrike AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
